2 et 3. Choisir les groupes de variables

library(FactoMineR)
afm <- MFA(QteVie, group = c(5,5,3,6,3,1), type = c(rep("s",5),"n"), name.group = c("Bien-tre matriel","Emploi","Satisfaction","Sant et scurit","Enseignement","Rgion"), num.group.sup = 6)

4. Choisir le nombre daxes

barplot(afm$eig[,2], names = paste("Dim", 1:nrow(afm$eig)))

5. Analyser les rsultats

summary(afm, nbelement = 10, nb.dec = 2, ncp = 2)

     "Satisfaction", "Sant et scurit", "Enseignement", "Rgion"),  
     num.group.sup = 6)
